<TEXT>Your browser is unsupported We recommend using the latest version of IE11, Edge, Chrome, Firefox or Safari. University of Illinois Chicago Search the site University of Illinois Chicago Transportation Main Menu Expand Buses menu Expand Paratransit menu Expand Night Ride menu Expand Vehicles menu Eyebrow menu Administrative Services UIC menu UIC.edu Campus Map Search Down arrow icon Night Ride The UIC Night Ride provides safe and dependable after-hours transportation services for students, staff and authorized UIC community members. Heading link xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link The UIC Night Ride service allows the UIC community to travel safely within campus boundaries after the operational hours of UIC buses and shuttles. Comprised of four 15-passenger vans, the services provides an on-demand option for students and staff to use after hours. Pickups can be arranged at any campus facility and transport you to other campus locations return to your own residence provided it falls within the boundaries of the service. The Night Ride also provides direct service to UIC Law. To request Night Ride service, users must download the TransLoc app . For more information, email rides@uic.com or call (312) 996-2842. All riders need a valid UIC i-card Heading link xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link 7 days a week | 365 days a year | 11 p.m. – 7 a.m Night Ride Back to main content Coverage Area Code of Conduct Setting up and using a TransLōc Account Feedback University of Illinois Chicago Policies Web Privacy Notice Related Links Facilities Management Office of the Vice Chancellor of Administrative Services Social Media Accounts Contact 1351 South Morgan Street, Chicago, IL 60608 Phone: (312) 996-2842 Fax: (312) 996-0165 rides@uic.edu UIC.edu links UIC.edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Event Calendar Job Openings Library Maps UIC Safe Mobile App UIC Today UI Healt